    • Method Detail

      • tanksByBottom

        public java.util.NavigableMap<java.lang.Double,java.util.Set<Tank>> tanksByBottom()
        Returns a NavigableMap that associates to each break point in the system, the set of tanks whose bottom is exactly at the break point. It looks through each tank in the system and adds them to the NavigableMap. If the bottom height of the tank is already in the NavigableMap, the Set of Tanks for that key is pulled out, added to the set, and put back in the NavigableMap. If the break point is new, a new Set is created.
        Returns:
        the map of all tanks and their bottom heights

      • tanksByTop

        public java.util.NavigableMap<java.lang.Double,java.util.Set<Tank>> tanksByTop()
        Returns a NavigableMap that associates to each break point in the system, the set of tanks whose top is exactly at the break point. It looks through each tank in the system and adds them to the NavigableMap. If the top height of the tank is already in the NavigableMap, the Set of Tanks for that key is pulled out, added to the set, and put back in the NavigableMap. If the break point is new, a new Set is created.
        Returns:
        the map of all tanks and their top heights

      • activeTanks

        public java.util.NavigableMap<java.lang.Double,java.util.Set<Tank>> activeTanks()
        At each break point in the system, check each tank in the system. If the bottom of the tank is less than or equal to the break point and if the top is greater than it, the tank is added to a set that is then associated to the corresponding break point.
        Returns:
        a map that associates each break point to its active tanks

      • activeBaseArea

        public java.util.NavigableMap<java.lang.Double,java.lang.Double> activeBaseArea()
        Checks every break point in the system. If a tank is active at that point, it's base area is added to a temporary count. When the break point is done being checked, the association is added to the map.
        Returns:
        a NavigableMap associating the break points to the active base area when the water is at that break point level.

      • heightToTankLevel

        public java.util.Map<Tank,java.lang.Double> heightToTankLevel(java.lang.Double waterHeight)
        Returns a map that associates each tank with the level, as measured from the tank base, to which the tank is filled, assuming the given water height in the system. It checks every tank that has water in it based on the method filledTanksAtHeight.
        Parameters:
        waterHeight - The level of the water in the system
        Returns:
        A map that associates each tank with the level to which the tank is filled

      • partFullTanks

        private java.util.Set<Tank> partFullTanks(java.lang.Double waterVolume)
        For each tank in the system, as long as the volume of water in the system is less than the volume of the water level at the top of the tank and greater than if it was at the bottom of the tank, it can be inferred that the tank has water in it, but is not full
        Parameters:
        waterVolume - volume of water in the system
        Returns:
        set of tanks that are partially full

      • volFullTanks

        private java.lang.Double volFullTanks(java.lang.Double waterVolume)
        If the volume of water in the system is greater than the volume of water in the system if the height of the water was at the top of a tank, we can infer that that tank is full of water. By adding all of their volumes, we have the combined volume of all full tanks in the system
        Parameters:
        waterVolume - volume of water in the system
        Returns:
        volume of water only in completely full tanks

      • partFullTanksHelperNumbers

        private double[] partFullTanksHelperNumbers(java.util.Set<Tank> partFullTanks)
        Finds the partially filled tank with a bottom higher than any other partially filled tank and finds the total base area of all the partially filled tanks
        Parameters:
        partFullTanks - set of tanks that are partially filled
        Returns:
        array containing the highest bottom of a tank and the total base area of all partially filled tanks
